net.hudup.core.data

Class ExternalItemInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.ExternalItemInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class ExternalItemInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, TextParsable, Cloneable
    Items represent many kinds of goods such as books, clothes. The Hudup database cannot store all information about various goods. So this class called external item information stores additional information about items that are not stored in Hudup database. For example, cover image of a book is an external information. In other words, external item information is a record of item, stored in outside database different from Hudup database.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
